":2,"relpermalink":"/post/questions/","section":"post","summary":"Not often, but sometimes, you stumble upon a question that is so profound to you that you would almost be sad to find the answer. It keeps you searching yourself, calling upon something deeper than rote learning or textbook memorization.\nPerhaps we can call these “floating questions.” They evade scientific explanation.\nFloating questions demand an answer from your life. They can generate enormous passion, send humans into space, and create beautiful art.","tags":null,"title":"Questions to be lived","type":"post","url":"/post/questions/","weight":0,"wordcount":246},{"author":null,"categories":null,"content":null,"date":1609891200,"description":"","dir":"","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":100,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"term","lang":"en","lastmod":1609891200,"objectID":"","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/categories/shorter/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":0,"relpermalink":"/categories/shorter/","section":"categories","summary":"","tags":null,"title":"Shorter","type":"categories","url":"/categories/shorter/","weight":0,"wordcount":0},{"author":null,"categories":["Shorter"],"content":null,"date":1609804800,"description":"","dir":"post/","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":300,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1609804800,"objectID":"0aff97c890c1e15baf0ebc1744e15ca4","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/post/goodday/","publishdate":"2021-01-05T00:00:00Z","readingtime":2,"relpermalink":"/post/goodday/","section":"post","summary":"One golden afternoon last October, while taking a walk, I wrote a thought down: \u0026ldquo;Eventually, my life will just be as good as my days. So I need to enjoy my days if I am going to enjoy my life.\u0026quot;\nEmbedded in there is the idea that no one state or achievement will likely \u0026ldquo;make\u0026rdquo; my