 in life to go all out.\nLast year, I went all out on a 50-mile hike alone, completing it in 19 hours.\nI learned some invaluable lessons like\n Don\u0026rsquo;t trust Google maps over mountains (I got lost) Always pack an extra almond poppyseed muffin. Stopping to rest only makes your legs hurt more.  More importantly, I learned that after being alone and exhausted for hours, all the noise in your head quiets down, and you come to know yourself and your limits.","tags":["life lessons"],"title":"Moderation in moderation","type":"post","url":"/post/moderation/","weight":0,"wordcount":292},{"author":null,"categories":null,"content":null,"date":-62135596800,"description":"","dir":"","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":100,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"term","lang":"en","lastmod":-62135596800,"objectID":"","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/tags/plato/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":0,"relpermalink":"/tags/plato/","section":"tags","summary":"","tags":null,"title":"Plato","type":"tags","url":"/tags/plato/","weight":0,"wordcount":0},{"author":null,"categories":["Longer"],"content":null,"date":-62135596800,"description":"","dir":"post/","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":1000,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":-62135596800,"objectID":"93d31b8d0927f0d1f87ed79925a35ae1","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/post/plato/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":5,"relpermalink":"/post/plato/","section":"post","summary":"Almost 2400 years ago, one of the greatest revolutions the western world has ever known set off.\nIt was a relatively quiet explosion, not a famous battle or the overthrow of an empire. It was a young man watching his hero, teacher, and mentor put on trial and condemned to death. His teacher had dedicated his life to questioning others, for, as he put it, \u0026ldquo;the unexamined life is not worth living.","tags":["Plato","ordinary"],"title":"Plato, the moral revolutionary","type":"post","url":"/post/plato/","weight":0,"wordcount":926},{"author":null,"categories":null,"content":"Archive of historical posts.","date":-62135596800,"description":"Archive of historical posts.","dir":"top/","excerpt_html":"Archive of historical posts.","excerpt_text":"Archive of historical posts.","expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":100,"html":"Archive of historical posts.","keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":-62135596800,"objectID":"104f9431647fd5dcb14e8d0947747fa9","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/top/archive/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":0,"relpermalink":"/top/archive/","section":"top","summary":"","tags":null,"title":"Posts Archive","type":"post","url":"/top/archive/","weight":0,"wordcount":0},{"author":null,"categories":null,"content":null,"date":-62135596800,"description":"","dir":"","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":100,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"section","lang":"en","lastmod":-62135596800,"objectID":"","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/search/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":0,"relpermalink":"/search/","section":"search","summary":"","tags":null,"title":"Searches","type":"search","url":"/search/","weight":0,"wordcount":0},{"author":null,"categories":null,"content":null,"date":-62135596800,"description":"","dir":"post/","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":400,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":-62135596800,"objectID":"ba83a0668c3bc3744d92e38b94640ad8","permalink":"https://nathancheever.com/post/talk/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":2,"relpermalink":"/post/talk/","section":"post","summary":"As an introvert, small talk has never come easy for me. I enjoy watching the occasional football or basketball game. Still, I can\u0026rsquo;t talk at length 